comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T12:14:06.396Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check: searched all pm statuses for GHSA-3jxr-9vmj-r5cp,CVE-2026-13149,brace-expansion,and Dependabot alert #42; no canonical item exists. GitHub alert #42 is open/high,affects transitive development brace-expansion 5.0.6 through minimatch/ESLint,and identifies 5.0.7 as the first patched 5.x release. No open dependency PR exists."
  "2026-07-21T12:18:39.430Z",codex-root,"Verification correction: the first linked matrix proved coverage, frozen install, and audit, but the generic command pnpm validate:release does not exist in pm-cli and failed before any gate. Replacing it with this repository's canonical pnpm release:gates contract; this is a test-link configuration error, not a product regression."
  "2026-07-21T12:54:31.299Z",codex-root,"Evidence: pnpm audit --audit-level high reports no known vulnerabilities; pnpm install --frozen-lockfile is reproducible; 332 test files and 6,059 tests pass with statements/branches/functions/lines all exactly 100%; static quality, 100% docstrings, package boundary, token budget, jscpd zero-clone, and tracked-secret gates pass. The earlier release:gates failure is isolated to live Sentry issues PM-CLI-2D/2E and will be rerun after this PR merges and those commit-scoped issues are resolved. GitHub Dependabot alert #42 must be confirmed closed on the merged head."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T12:54:31.917Z",codex-root,"Release sequencing: do not reuse or move the existing same-day v2026.7.21 tag. Verify alert #42 against the merged commit and let the next automatic daily release include the patched lockfile."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T12:54:32.662Z",codex-root,"A narrow pnpm override floor is an effective transitive advisory control only when paired with frozen-lockfile proof, pnpm audit, and post-merge GitHub alert verification."
